Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.73,0:05:21.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,某些现象我认为显然只是由于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the events that I've seen are clearly just due to turbulence
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.73,0:05:24.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球大气的扰动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.07,0:05:27.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,扰动造成了月球的移动和变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These cause movement and change on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.53,0:05:32.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是布拉蒂认为不是所有的月球瞬变现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Buratti thinks that not all LTPs
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.91,0:05:37.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都能用大气扰动来解释\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can be explained by atmospheric turbulence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:40.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尼尔·阿姆斯特朗所报告的现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The anomalies that Neil Armstrong reported
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.34,0:05:42.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是在月球表面看到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were seen from the lunar surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.38,0:05:46.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以大气扰动不可能造成这种现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so atmospheric turbulence couldn't be causing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.88,0:05:49.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,许多天文学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many astronomers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.05,0:05:51.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,像格利菲斯天文台的劳拉·丹利\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like Laura Danly at the Griffith Observatory,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.01,0:05:54.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,认为流星和小行星的高速作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}believe that the high-velocity impact of meteors and asteroids
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.68,0:06:00.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,解释了地球上所观察到的这个现象的主要原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}accounts for much of this activity being observed from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.81,0:06:01.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们移动得非常得快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're traveling very fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.94,0:06:04.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以当它们轰击月球时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so when they smash into the Moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.82,0:06:14.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,确实是一个猛烈明亮的爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a big, bright explosion, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.12,0:06:17.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些碰撞爆炸被认为是火球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These impact explosions, known as fireballs,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.87,0:06:19.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能是那现象的一个原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be one source of the activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.96,0:06:23.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是前提是存在一个漏洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that premise has a gaping hole in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.63,0:06:27.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使我们已经看到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though we've seen
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.63,0:06:29.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球阴暗面的那些闪烁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these flashes on the dark side of the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.30,0:06:33.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们还是没有确定与之相联系的陨石坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we haven't identified a crater associated with any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.76,0:06:36.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就让我们陷入了争议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's where we get into the controversy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.02,0:06:38.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,没有任何大的事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There hasn't been any large event
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.89,0:06:42.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被确切地观察到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that has been unequivocally observed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.94,0:06:45.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,另一个可能的解释是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another possible explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.61,0:06:47.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当流星击中月球时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that when a meteor hits the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.61,0:06:49.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,形成了巨大的陨石坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it creates a massive crater.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.57,0:06:51.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,围绕着陨石坑边缘的山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Landslides around the crater
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.78,0:06:55.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,崩抬起了月球尘埃的山体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rim kick up mountains of lunar dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.08,0:06:58.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,纤细的尘埃会吸收和散射光线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The fine dust could absorb and scatter light rays
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:07:00.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或呈现出好象月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or make it appear as if the Moon has
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.00,0:07:04.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,某种程度改变了表面特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}somehow changed its surface features.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.00,0:07:08.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有可能一旦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's possible that if
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.09,0:07:09.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球表面发生山崩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a landslide occurred on the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.30,0:07:11.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就会在地球上看到某种现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you would see something from the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.59,0:07:13.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,陨石坑边缘被遮掩了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the edge of a crater being obscured,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.18,0:07:15.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,形成云状的现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a cloud-like feature forming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.85,0:07:18.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,换句话说我们将看到陨石坑壁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In other words, we would see a crater wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.56,0:07:21.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是月球瞬变现象 接着陨石坑壁垮塌了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an LTP, and then a collapsed crater wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.85,0:07:23.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们一直没有看到过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've never seen that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.86,0:07:34.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许在那些月球异常\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps the most controversial
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:36.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现象背后最具争议的争议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}theory behind these lunar anomalies
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.28,0:07:39.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将改变我们对月球的整个看法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could alter our view of the Moon entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.83,0:07:45.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它将挑战信念 即月球已经停止地质活动有几千年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would challenge the belief that the Moon has been geologically inactive for millennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.88,0:07:49.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其中一个对月球瞬变现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the most intriguing explanations
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.21,0:07:50.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最耐人寻味的解释\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for lunar transient phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.92,0:07:53.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是月球上有活火山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is active volcanoes on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.64,0:08:03.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是最科学的重要理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the most scientifically important
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.06,0:08:04.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为它将告诉我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it would tell us that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.10,0:08:08.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球的地质仍然是活跃的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Moon is still geologically active.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.86,0:08:13.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,阿波罗太空任务期间所拍摄的照片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Photographs taken during the Apollo space missions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.70,0:08:16.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,揭示了形成于月球表面的岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}revealed a rocky formation on the lunar surface
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.53,0:08:18.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是所谓的"非结构的"(inastructure)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called the "inastructure."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.83,0:08:21.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对于这个资料科学家推测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With this data, scientists speculated
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.25,0:08:24.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球可能经历火山活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the Moon could have experienced volcanic activity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.42,0:08:28.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是在过去的数百万年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the last million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.75,0:08:30.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个信息具有突破性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The information was groundbreaking and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.55,0:08:32.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它意味着火山活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it meant that volcanic activity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.42,0:08:35.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能是月球瞬变现象主要起因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could be the primary source of LTPs,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.59,0:08:39.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是大多数科学家尚存疑虑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but most scientists are yet to be convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.52,0:08:44.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在科学上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The thing about science is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.77,0:08:47.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每当你有了一个理论或者模型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whenever you have a theory or a model,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.52,0:08:50.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你必须能够获取其结果的数据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you have to be able to get data of an event
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.94,0:08:53.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一遍又一遍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.36,0:08:57.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在那些更加神秘的增亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In terms of these more mysterious brightenings
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.78,0:08:59.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或有可能是火山活动的情况方面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or things that could be volcanic events,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.87,0:09:03.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,实际上我们从来没有两个独立的观察者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we've never actually had two independent observers
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:06.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在同一时刻获得无可争辩的数据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}obtain incontrovertible data at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.13,0:09:16.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使月球上没有地质活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even if the Moon isn't geologically active,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.80,0:09:20.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些天文学家认为 可能会有气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some astronomers believe there may be gases left over
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.35,0:09:24.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在当时火山活动频繁时残留了下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from a time when the volcanic activity was prevalent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.64,0:09:28.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果残留的气体到达表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If residual gases reach the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.15,0:09:30.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳光会散射出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun's rays would scatter
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.65,0:09:34.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,气体粒子红与蓝的色彩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}colored hues of red and blue from the gas particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.53,0:09:36.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球仍然可能在经历着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon could still be experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.11,0:09:39.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,排气而内部实际上没有活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}outgassing without having actual activity in the interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.53,0:09:42.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球里的矿物产生着气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are minerals in the Moon that produce gases, and they seep up
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.58,0:09:46.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们渗透出月球的表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the surface in the Moon and come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.75,0:09:52.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有这么多的月球瞬变现象理论摆在面前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With so many lunar transient phenomena theories out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.50,0:09:54.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,哪一个是最合理的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is the most plausible?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.67,0:09:57.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,布拉蒂博士没有明确哪一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dr. Buratti doesn't point to one
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.59,0:09:59.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,适合于现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}explanation for the phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.14,0:10:02.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为月球瞬变现象的原因可能有无数个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think the reasons for LTP are probably myriad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.68,0:10:05.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为存在不止一个的解释\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think there's more than one explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.22,0:10:07.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它不只是一种现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not just one phenomenon,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.27,0:10:10.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能是许多不同类型的活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's many different types of activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.27,0:10:13.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,目前 难以捉摸的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For now, the cause of the elusive
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.11,0:10:15.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球瞬变现象的起因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lunar transient phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:18.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能继续隐藏在月球的阴暗面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may remain hidden on the dark side of the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.99,0:10:24.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而满月导致地球上狂热的起因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the cause of full Moon fever here on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.79,0:10:28.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,诊断起来甚至更加棘手\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be even tougher to diagnose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.79,0:10:34.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果有的话那满月对我们的身心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What role, if any,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.21,0:10:37.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,究竟有什么作用？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}does the full Moon have on our bodies and our minds?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.85,0:10:47.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当提到探究月球之谜时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it comes to exploring the mysteries of the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.89,0:10:50.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也许最著名和最具争议的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps the most celebrated and controversial
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.77,0:10:56.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的卫星是否对身心有什么影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is whether our satellite has any influence on the mind and body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.40,0:11:00.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们知道地球与月球之间存在某种关系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that there's some relationship between the Earth and the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.28,0:11:02.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此或许不是明显地突现 在想象中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so, it's perhaps not such a great leap to imagine that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.57,0:11:03.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有不同的变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the different changes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.87,0:11:08.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,满月可能会对人产生某种影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the full Moon might have some influence on people.
