Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.77,0:16:25.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,基于个人经验的基础上的偏见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's based on personal experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.27,0:16:26.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你留意证据 你会发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you look at the evidence, you find
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.90,0:16:30.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,真的没有明确的机制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there really is no clear mechanism
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.57,0:16:32.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来说明月球的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the influence of the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.74,0:16:35.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,与人体健康与疾病的关系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with health and disease in human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.91,0:16:39.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过 还是继续有精明的医生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nevertheless, there continue to be astute clinicians
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.54,0:16:41.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,作为仔细的观察家在坚持\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and careful observers who insist
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.54,0:16:44.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,自己看到了那关系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they do see relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.67,0:16:47.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,驱使人们行为的是他们所相信的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}People's behavior is driven by what they believe
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.67,0:16:50.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你相信月球有一些神奇之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and if you believe there is something magical about the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.42,0:16:54.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它掌握着对你的魔咒的话 那么或许你就会改变自己的行为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it holds a spell over you then perhaps you will change your behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.97,0:16:56.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不管满月是否\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whether the full Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.09,0:16:58.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对身心具有明显的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has any measurable impact on body and mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.97,0:17:01.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都将继续是争论的起因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will continue to be a source of debate
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.47,0:17:05.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和我们月亮神话的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and part of the mythology of our Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.10,0:17:08.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,围绕着我们最近的邻居\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there are other mythological legends
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:10.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还有其它神话传说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}surrounding our closest neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.77,0:17:12.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管那样不是每个人都能够看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even then, not everyone can see
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.74,0:17:15.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球上的"人"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the man in the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.32,0:17:21.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是那些巨大的暗的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The man on the Moon are these giant dark
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.49,0:17:23.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,创作出来的 有些人认为看上去像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}areas that create what some people think looks like
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.00,0:17:25.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,眼球 鼻子和笑脸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}eyeballs and a nose, and smiley face.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.00,0:17:32.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我先表明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let me begin by saying
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.09,0:17:35.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我从来没有见到过月球上的人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that I have never seen the man on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.68,0:17:40.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,人们怎样才能看到它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And how anyone can see it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.35,0:17:46.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,关键在于主观创造性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a matter of...subjective creativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.56,0:17:51.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月亮长期以来一直就是传说和神话的对象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon has long been the object of lore and myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:53.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是我们认为我们所看到的全部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what we think we see is all
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.19,0:17:56.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是观看者眼中的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.53,0:18:01.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,多数文化其实并没有看到月球上的人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most cultures actually don't see a man on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.41,0:18:03.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,兔子是许多人的宠物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rabbit is a big favorite among many
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:05.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还有其它的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and there are others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.00,0:18:14.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而大家举头望月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But everyone who looks up at the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.13,0:18:18.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可以看到月球表面的明亮 昏暗的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can see light and dark areas on the lunar surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.97,0:18:20.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些不是幻觉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these are not an illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.39,0:18:24.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是非常真实的高山和峡谷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but very real mountains and valleys.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.85,0:18:27.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,明亮的区域是崎岖 多坑的高地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The light areas are rugged, cratered highlands
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.68,0:18:31.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,叫做"terrae" 拉丁语的"土地"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}known as, "terrae," Latin for "lands".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.11,0:18:33.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,高地是月球原始地壳的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The highlands are part of the Moon's original crust
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.69,0:18:36.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,遭受到流星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was shattered by the impact of meteoroids,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.36,0:18:38.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,小行星 彗星的冲击破坏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}asteroids, and comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:43.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球上昏暗的区域叫做"maria"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The darker areas on the Moon are known as "maria".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.20,0:18:47.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,"Maria"的意思是"海"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Mare" is a word meaning "sea".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.54,0:18:50.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是远古的熔岩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are ancient lava beds that were
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.21,0:18:56.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从前是流动的 但现在已经凝固了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at one time flowing, but are now solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.09,0:18:59.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,形成于几十亿年前的火山喷发影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Formed from impact cratering over billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.22,0:19:03.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月海的面积占了月球表面的16%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the maria account for 16 percent of the Moon surface
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.05,0:19:06.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看上去像水体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and look like bodies of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.43,0:19:09.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最新的看法是有巨大的小行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The latest thinking is that giant asteroids
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.35,0:19:10.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,击中了月球的另外一面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hit the other side of the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.98,0:19:13.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,震撼着月球非常地醒目\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and rocked the Moon so significantly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.94,0:19:17.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,熔岩在我们所看到的这一面渗透出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that lava oozed out of the side that we see
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.28,0:19:21.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,形成了这些大片的昏暗的熔岩区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and created these big dark expanses of lava
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.28,0:19:23.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当然随着时间推移凝固了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that of course, solidified over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.71,0:19:32.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,形成明暗对比的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ancient volcanic activity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.25,0:19:35.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,远古火山活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that formed the contrasts of dark and light
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.50,0:19:37.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被无意的中创造出 看上去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have inadvertently created what some see
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.75,0:19:42.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,像是人面特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the features of a human face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.60,0:19:46.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,眼球实际上是雨海(Mare Imbrium)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The eyeballs are actually the Mare Imbrium,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.93,0:19:48.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和静海(Mare Serenitatis)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sea of rains
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.77,0:19:54.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,意思是宁静之海\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Mare Serenitatis which means sea of serenity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.94,0:20:00.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,鼻子是暑湾(Sinus Aestuum) 意思是巨浪之湾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nose is the Sinus Aestuum, which means bay of billows.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.90,0:20:03.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大嘴是云海(Mare Nubium)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the open mouth is the Mare Nubium,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.42,0:20:08.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和认知海(Mare Cognitum)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the sea of clouds and the Mare Cognitum,or sea of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:10.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,人们看到月球上的"人"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For humans to see a man on the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.00,0:20:14.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能是源于我们试图了解月球奥秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be our way of trying to understand the lunar mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.25,0:20:18.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以及我们与之不可分割联系在一起的缘故\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and how we're inextricably connected to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.92,0:20:22.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,许多月球之谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many mysteries of the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.47,0:20:26.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,已经深刻地影响到了我们的文明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have influenced our civilization in dramatic ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.72,0:20:28.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,古人将历法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ancient man based his calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.76,0:20:32.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,农业 数学以及天文学\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}agriculture, mathematics,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.98,0:20:38.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,建立在不断交替但始终一贯的月相上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and astronomy...on the changing but consistent phases of the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.19,0:20:42.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在每个月里月球表现出在8个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every month, the Moon appears to change its shape
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.15,0:20:45.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月相循环周期上变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}during an eight phase spin cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.91,0:20:50.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为什么月球会有月相？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why does the Moon have phases?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.00,0:20:54.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月相的发生是因为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The phases of the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.33,0:20:58.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球围绕着地球旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}occur because as the Moon orbits around the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.88,0:21:04.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们看到的是它明亮一面的圆缺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we see more or less of its lit side.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.38,0:21:06.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们看到的月球反射出来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The light we see being reflected from the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.76,0:21:11.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,光实际上是来自太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is actually coming from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.64,0:21:13.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,想象一下太阳在这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine the Sun is over there
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.27,0:21:14.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this is the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.31,0:21:15.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this is the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.85,0:21:20.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当月球被太阳完全照亮时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Moon is fully lit by the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.86,0:21:24.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就能看到它的亮面 那是满月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we can see that lit side, it's a full Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.07,0:21:26.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着月球围绕着地球运行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the Moon goes around the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.20,0:21:28.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们看到亮面越来越小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we see less and less
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.57,0:21:32.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而暗面越来越大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the lit side and more and more of the dark side.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.83,0:21:36.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,满月时月球是在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The full Moon occurs when the Moon is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.71,0:21:39.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳到地球的对面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the opposite side of the Earth from the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.88,0:21:45.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,面对我们的月球表面整个被照亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the lunar surface facing us is fully lit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.72,0:21:47.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月相的样子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The shapes of the phases of the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.43,0:21:51.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是由于我们在地球上观察的角度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are due to our perspective on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.56,0:21:56.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看到的是月球亮面的多与少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seeing more or less of the lit side of the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.02,0:21:58.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实不然 比如\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not a case of...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.82,0:22:05.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球遮挡了一些会照到月球的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for example, the Earth blocking some of the...light that would have otherwise struck the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.53,0:22:09.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不管怎样确实发生了月食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That does occur, however, during an eclipse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.87,0:22:13.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球上远看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that terrestrial perspective
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.08,0:22:16.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时会捉弄我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can sometimes play tricks on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.66,0:22:18.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当提起月球的大小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it comes to the Moon size,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.87,0:22:22.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,视觉会被蒙骗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}looks can be deceiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.51,0:22:28.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一些月球之谜很难理解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the Moon's mysteries are difficult to comprehend
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.84,0:22:32.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的眼睛告诉我们的是一回事 而科学告诉的则是另一回事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when our eyes tell us one thing and science, another.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.22,0:22:36.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们只是需要对问题不同的视角\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We just need a different perspective on the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.27,0:22:39.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时满月在空中升起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sometimes when the full Moon rises in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.27,0:22:42.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在地平线附近看上去要比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it appears much larger near the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.77,0:22:46.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它在空中更高的地方来得大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than it does when it's positioned higher in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.11,0:22:47.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些观察者判断月球在刚出现时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some observers judge the Moon to be as much as
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.78,0:22:52.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,要大出50到75%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}50 to 75 percent larger when it first appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.57,0:22:57.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么满月在地平线附近时真的要大点吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but is the full Moon really larger when it's near the horizon?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.20,0:23:00.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我的朋友都认为月亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My friends all think that the Moon is bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.08,0:23:01.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在地平线上时要更大些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it's on the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.71,0:23:04.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为月亮在地平线上时要更大些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think that the Moon is bigger when it's on the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.25,0:23:08.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么是什么原因造成了看上去会如此不同呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So what could be causing it to look so different?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.72,0:23:11.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球并没有真正改变它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon doesn't really change its apparent size
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.64,0:23:16.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从地平线到头顶的外观大小 但我们的视觉却是它要大些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the horizon to overhead. but our perception is that it's larger.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.14,0:23:19.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一种理论认为我们的头脑里判断月亮的大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One theory is that our mind judges the Moon's size
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.81,0:23:22.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是与其它的物体有关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in relation to other objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.81,0:23:25.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在地平线上看上去大些是因为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It looks much larger at the horizon because
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.23,0:23:27.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,存在着我们能够与其相比较的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there are things we can compare it to,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.48,0:23:28.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而在头顶上时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whereas at the top of the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.57,0:23:32.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是其早已熟悉的自身形象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's out there by its little old self.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.74,0:23:34.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,换句话说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.83,0:23:38.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我们看到被月球比下去的 像房子那样大的物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if we see a large object such as a house dwarfed by the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.79,0:23:42.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的大脑里就会告诉我们月球必然非常巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our mind tells us that the Moon must be enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.83,0:23:47.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而当月球孤身出现时 我们的大脑就不会作出那样的判断\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But when the Moon is out by itself, our mind doesn't make that assumption,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.17,0:23:51.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看到的月球就很小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we see the Moon as small.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.51,0:23:55.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,另一种可能性是庞邹错觉引起的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another possible cause of this is the Ponzo illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.14,0:23:57.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是以马里奥·庞邹的名字命名的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}named after Mario Ponzo,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.14,0:24:00.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他提出大脑判断一个物体的大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who suggested that the mind judges the size of an object
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.43,0:24:03.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是基于它的背景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}based on its background.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.73,0:24:06.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,庞邹画出两条相同的线条\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ponzo drew two identical bars
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.06,0:24:08.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,横跨在随着距离消退的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}across a picture of railroad tracks
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.28,0:24:10.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,铁路轨道的图片上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as they recede in the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.11,0:24:11.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,上面的线条看上去要宽些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The upper bars look wider
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.57,0:24:14.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是因为它们看上去跨过了铁轨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they appear to span the rails,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.20,0:24:17.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相对下面的线条恰好在铁轨之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compared to the lower bars, which fits between the rails.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.99,0:24:21.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而事实上骑跨在铁轨上的线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in fact, the lines overlaid on the tracks
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.00,0:24:25.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,两端的尺寸是一样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the same size at both ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.88,0:24:31.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,带着一支铅笔到户外去 当月亮升起时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Go out and take a pencil, and when the Moon is rising,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.88,0:24:35.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,拿上铅笔 伸出手臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}put the pencil out at arms length and see how big the Moon is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.39,0:24:39.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看月亮相对铅笔上橡皮头有多大 然后几个小时后再出去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compared to the eraser on the pencil, and then go out a couple of hours later
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.89,0:24:41.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在月亮升得更高时再做一遍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and do the same thing when the Moon is higher in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.39,0:24:43.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就会看到在两个时段里月亮相对铅笔的橡皮头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you'll see that the Moon is exactly the same size
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.02,0:24:48.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大小实际上是一样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in relation to the pencil eraser at both times.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.82,0:24:58.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当提起月亮的大小时可能会把我们戏弄一下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon may play tricks with us when it comes to judging its size,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.03,0:25:03.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是它对我们地球的影响可不是虚构的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but there is nothing imaginary about its effects on our Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.88,0:25:18.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在所有隐蔽的月球之谜中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of all the hidden lunar mysteries,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.05,0:25:22.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有一个是刚好能够在地球上观察到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is one that can be observed right here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.43,0:25:26.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这可能是能归咎于月球的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It may be the most influential phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.44,0:25:28.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最有影响力的现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can be attributed to the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.28,0:25:33.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在我们的地球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From our place on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.65,0:25:36.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,潮汐每天有规律地出现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tides just appear to be the times of day when the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.28,0:25:38.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其时海水涨落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sea rises and falls.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.28,0:25:41.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过那是个相互作用 引力的相互作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that's an interaction, a gravitational interaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.58,0:25:42.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在月球与地球之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between the Moon and the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.79,0:25:45.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此当月球经过时…\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so when the Moon is passing by...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.71,0:25:48.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它拉动海洋 把它抬起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It pulls on the oceans and pulls it up higher
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.58,0:25:51.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这时我们看到了一个高潮位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we see it as a high tide.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.21,0:25:55.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海洋潮汐是由\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ocean tides are caused
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.92,0:26:00.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳和月球的引力引起的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the gravitational pull of the Sun and our Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.80,0:26:03.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳和月球两者吸引着地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun and the Moon both pull on the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.22,0:26:04.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,造成了潮汐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and contribute to tides.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.52,0:26:05.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是月球要近得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the Moon is much closer so its pull of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.93,0:26:11.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以它的引力感觉到比太阳更强\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is felt more strongly than the Sun's.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.02,0:26:13.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海洋学家Tetjana Ross\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oceanographer Tetjana Ross
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.48,0:26:17.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,称月球永恒不变地拽着地球是很可怕的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}says the Moon's constant tug on the Earth is formidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.57,0:26:20.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球的影响在潮汐中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The reason that the Moon's influence
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.20,0:26:22.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如此明显的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is so visible in the form of tides
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.53,0:26:24.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是因为水能够…\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is because water can...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.43,0:26:28.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,流动 水是柔性的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}run, it can move. it's malleable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.33,0:26:32.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在加拿大一个偏远的海湾里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a remote bay in Canada,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.46,0:26:34.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个社区已经学会了与神秘极端的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one community has learned to live
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.37,0:26:37.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海洋潮汐共同生活\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with mysterious and extreme ocean tides
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.34,0:26:41.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种潮汐是地球上其它地方看不到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are found nowhere else on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.51,0:26:45.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然普通的潮汐涨起平均是3英尺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While normal tides rise by an average of three feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.43,0:26:47.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是在新斯科舍和新不伦瑞克\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the waters along the bay of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.68,0:26:49.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,之间的芬迪湾的海水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fundy between Nova Scotia and New Brunswick
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.89,0:26:54.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每天两次涨起50英尺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}swell up to 50 feet twice every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.69,0:26:58.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,芬迪湾涨起这么大的潮汐的原因之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the reasons the bay of Fundy has such large tides
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.70,0:27:02.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是因为海湾下面的地形地貌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is because of the shape of the landforms underneath the bay
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.16,0:27:03.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它是漏斗形的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's kind of a funnel shaped,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.87,0:27:07.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只要水面抬起 它就迅速升起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so as the water level rises it really rises rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.87,0:27:11.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,高潮来时1000亿吨海水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At high tide, a hundred billion tons of water
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.50,0:27:15.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在一个小时左右涌进海湾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sloshes into the bay in a matter of hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.13,0:27:16.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后在退潮时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then during low tide,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.30,0:27:20.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大部分海水象浴缸一样排出去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most of it drains out like a bathtub.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.09,0:27:21.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,形成的海湾就是这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The bay is shaped just so,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.55,0:27:24.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以最先的潮汐来到时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that the first tide comes in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.68,0:27:26.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就象波浪往前推\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like a wave and it moves along.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.77,0:27:29.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被顶回 来到口子上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reflects off the back and it comes out to the mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.23,0:27:30.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,刚好同时又一拨潮水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just at the same time as the next
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.18,0:27:36.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,赶来了 所以它们叠加了起来 对此我们称之为共振\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tide had built up and so they add up in what we call "resonance."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.15,0:27:39.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,潮汐共振恰好是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tidal resonance is just getting the...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.78,0:27:43.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,与高潮升起同时发生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rise of the high tides to coincide;
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.91,0:27:46.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,某些波长反映出来的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Certain wavelengths are reflected in a way that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.37,0:27:48.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们相互增强\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they reinforce each other
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.16,0:27:49.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相互放大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and amplify each other
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.58,0:27:52.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,潮汐因此而被加强了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the tide...is therefore amplified.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.92,0:27:55.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,芬迪湾独特的漏斗形状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The unique funnel shape of the bay of Fundy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.50,0:28:00.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,促使了这个共振和推高了潮位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}contributes to this resonance and the height of its tides.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.30,0:28:03.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海湾逐渐分裂成一系列的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The bay gradually splits into a series of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.34,0:28:10.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,内港与河叉约束了潮流 促成了奇特的潮汐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}basins and river junctions that restricts the tidal flow and contributes to the extraordinary tides.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.14,0:28:17.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,潮汐是我们星球永远和月球栓在一起的又一种形式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tides, one more way our planet is forever tied to the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.19,0:28:19.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而还没有因此结束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it doesn't end there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.95,0:28:24.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们知道月球的引力一直在拉扯着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that the Moon's gravity is constantly pulling up
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.36,0:28:32.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们地球的海洋 同时地球的引里也在拉扯着月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the Earth's oceans while the Earth's gravity pulls down on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.87,0:28:35.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太空中一切物体都在被别的物体拉扯着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everything in space is tugging on everything else
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.08,0:28:36.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此地球拉扯着月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so the Earth is tugging on the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.58,0:28:39.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而月球也拉扯着地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Moon is tugging on the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.76,0:28:43.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球拉扯我们的海洋是如此的强烈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon's gravitational pull on our oceans is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.38,0:28:50.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,造成了我们地球的两边所谓的"潮起"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it creates what's called a "tidal bulge" on both sides of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.39,0:28:52.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球吸引着地球的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon pulls on the Earth gravitationally and...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.98,0:28:55.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦这样它也拉扯着海洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it does so, it also pulls on the oceans that are sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.90,0:28:59.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,向它稍微有点隆起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stretched up a little bit toward it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.02,0:29:01.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它最先拉起地球的前面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it pulls preferentially on the front side of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.65,0:29:03.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把海洋拉向它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pushes, pulls the ocean toward it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.49,0:29:04.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后拉着地球有一点点缩小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then pulls the Earth a little bit less,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.99,0:29:06.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而在背面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in the backside,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.24,0:29:09.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海洋拉向月球没那么厉害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the ocean is not pulled quite as far toward the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.83,0:29:11.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以那就是为什么地球上会有两个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that's why there are two
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.59,0:29:16.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所谓的"潮起"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}bulges that are called "tidal bulges" on the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.50,0:29:20.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们辽阔的海洋上的潮汐隆起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tidal bulges on our vast oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.50,0:29:24.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,实际上影响到了地球的自转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually impact the Earth's rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.38,0:29:28.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,潮汐隆起是月球造成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This tidal bulge that's created by the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.68,0:29:31.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它朝着月球稍微有一点点突出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's moving out ahead of the Moon a little bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.77,0:29:34.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球实际上是往后拉着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Moon is actually pulling back
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.73,0:29:36.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个潮汐隆起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on this tidal bulge.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.69,0:29:39.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么当月球往后拉着这个潮汐隆起时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, when the Moon pulls back on this tidal bulge,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.27,0:29:42.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也在减缓地球的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that slows the Earth down.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.69,0:29:45.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,没有我们的月球 地球将旋转的快得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without our Moon, the Earth would spin much faster
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.70,0:29:47.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的一天将会短得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and our days would be much shorter.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.03,0:29:52.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这将影响到这个行星上生命的进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this would affect how life has evolved on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.21,0:29:57.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而这些潮汐的力量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But these tidal forces,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.50,0:29:59.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把地球栓在月球上的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which tie the Earth to the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.38,0:30:02.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可是双向作用的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}travel a two-way street.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.55,0:30:07.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们地球对月球也具有不可否认的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Earth also has an undeniable effect on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.93,0:30:09.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么如果月球上有水的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if the Moon had water on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.80,0:30:11.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球的引力也会造成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would the Earth's gravitational pull
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.47,0:30:14.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球海洋类似的潮汐吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cause similar tides on lunar oceans?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.56,0:30:16.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,答案是会的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The answer is yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.68,0:30:18.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上几十亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, billions of years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.98,0:30:22.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球上几乎全部是液体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Moon was almost entirely made up of liquid,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.94,0:30:24.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但不是水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but not water.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.61,0:30:27.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当月球刚刚诞生 非常年轻时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Moon was first formed and very young,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.95,0:30:31.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,完全是液体的岩石 岩浆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was entirely liquid rock, magma.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.07,0:30:36.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球曾经一直象天空中炽热的地狱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon would've been like a blazing inferno in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.00,0:30:40.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为岩石是液体的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And because the rock was liquid,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.83,0:30:43.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管还是岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even though it was rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.25,0:30:45.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球拉扯的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gravitational pull of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.80,0:30:47.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以及月球的轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the orbit of the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.05,0:30:50.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引起了液体岩石的潮汐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}caused the liquid rock to have tides,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.47,0:30:53.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就象如今地球上的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just like the water on the Earth today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.01,0:30:57.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着时间的推移 月球以及它的熔岩潮汐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over time, the Moon and its lava tides
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.52,0:31:00.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,冷却形成了固体的荒凉景色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cooled into a solid desolate landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.65,0:31:02.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是地球与月球之间的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the gravitational relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.23,0:31:06.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力关系一直没有结束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between the Earth and the Moon has never ceased.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.36,0:31:10.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能够想象每个夜晚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But imagine if there was
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.20,0:31:12.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,没有了月亮露面的情景吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no Moon making an appearance each night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.20,0:31:14.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,世界将会有什么不同呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How different a world would it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.29,0:31:25.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们总是和这个叫做月球的神秘天体联系在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're always tied to this mysterious orb we call the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.63,0:31:31.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而一旦没有了月球 地球会有什么结果呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what would have happened to Earth if there were no Moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.05,0:31:35.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 我们存活到现在部分原因是由于月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The fact that we exist today is in part, due to the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.64,0:31:40.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一直在让地球打造\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}allowing the Earth to create
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.31,0:31:44.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们赖以生存的环境 早期的海洋 所有的矿物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the environment, the early oceans, all the minerals that allow us to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.36,0:31:48.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果从来就没有月球的话 现在的地球将是另外一个模样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If there had never been a Moon, Earth would be a different place today.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.36,0:31:52.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为月球引起了地球上的潮汐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because the Moon creates tides on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.57,0:31:55.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,塑造了我们的海岸线 景观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that shape our shorelines and shape the landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.46,0:32:07.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是月球影响我们进化的情形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's how the Moon impacted our evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.96,0:32:10.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大约4.5亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About 4 1/2 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.72,0:32:16.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球与地球之间的引力要比现在强好多好多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gravitational forces between the Moon and Earth were much stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.05,0:32:19.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当时月球已经形成 它距离地球要比现在近好多好多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Moon was formed, it was much, much closer to us than it is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.85,0:32:22.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它围绕地球旋转一周仅仅5个小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It took only five hours for it to orbit the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.35,0:32:26.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,由于它离得太近所以它在空中非常庞大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it was huge in the sky because it was so much closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.56,0:32:29.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球施加给地球的很强的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And more gravity exerted onto the Earth from a closer Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.94,0:32:34.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,意味着世界对我们的命运来说犹如一个物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}meant the world to our fate as a species.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.03,0:32:38.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在很近的月球的影响下 海洋第一次冲刷我们的星球时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When oceans first washed our planet under a closer Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.41,0:32:42.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,潮汐是今天的1000倍大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the tides were a thousand times greater than they are today.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.87,0:32:43.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你能想象得出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you could imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.92,0:32:47.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不是我们现在看到的10英尺的潮汐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that instead of having a 10-foot tide like we have today,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.25,0:32:49.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是1万英尺的潮汐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'd have a 10,000-foot tide.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.13,0:32:53.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此你就有了1万英尺的潮汐所冲刷的内陆了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, you would have 10,000-foot tides rushing inland.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.35,0:33:01.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些猛烈的潮汐有助于创造出适宜的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These intense tides helped create the right
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.39,0:33:05.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,海洋环境让生命得以发育\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}conditions in the oceans for life to develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.11,0:33:12.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,潮汐撕开了地壳坚硬的外层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tides ripped the outer layers of the crust
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.44,0:33:14.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,卷入了大海\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}off of the Earth, and put them into the oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.70,0:33:19.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,矿产丰富的汤汁 原始的汤汁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that mineral-rich soup, the primordial soup,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.33,0:33:25.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能够培育和进化生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was capable of developing and evolving life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.71,0:33:33.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些科学家认为潮水坑将是生命进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And some scientists believe that tidal pools would have been an ideal setting
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.97,0:33:38.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和适应陆地环境的理想之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for life to evolve and adapt to a terrestrial environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.89,0:33:42.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那将是个了不起的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would have been a great place,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.68,0:33:47.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如对于来自海洋的第一批生物长出自己的腿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for example, for the first...creatures from the sea to get their legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.77,0:33:49.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们可以来到潮水坑里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They could have come into a tidal pool where
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.44,0:33:52.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里干半天 湿半天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's wet half the day and dry half the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.19,0:33:54.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将是个非常棒的地方 能够长出你的腿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it would have been a great place to grow your legs
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.07,0:33:57.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并最终走向陆地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and eventually move onto land.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.16,0:34:01.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,按照天文学家尼尔·科明斯的说法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}According to astronomer Neil Comins,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.37,0:34:07.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们不能低估月球对我们作为一个物种进化的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can't underestimate the Moon's influence on our development as a species.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.25,0:34:09.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,若没有月球我不认为进化的过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without the Moon, I don't think that that process
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.63,0:34:12.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会如此的快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have occurred nearly as quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.34,0:34:16.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们已经进化到我们的生物钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have evolved so that our biological clocks
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.13,0:34:22.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,基于了大约23到24小时了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are based on around 23, 24-hour time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.47,0:34:26.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果月球从来没有过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the Moon had never existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.64,0:34:30.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么一天就将是6小时长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the day would be six hours long,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.98,0:34:37.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们作为生物是没法生存到现在的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we, as the creatures we are today, couldn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.70,0:34:41.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着月球减缓了地球的运行 稳定了我们的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the Moon slowed Earth's orbit, it stabilized our rotation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.57,0:34:45.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,影响到我们的气候和海洋潮汐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and affected our climate and ocean tides.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.41,0:34:48.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球极大地影响了哺乳动物的进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the Moon greatly influenced the development of mammals
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.25,0:34:51.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以它们的生存依赖于月光之夜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so dependent on Moonlit nights for their survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.79,0:34:55.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球对我们的生存确实产生了重大的影响了吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Has the Moon had a major impact on our existence?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.96,0:34:58.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我想 绝对是的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.05,0:35:04.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每次月圆时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every time the Moon is full,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.85,0:35:07.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球的模样是一模一样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the lunar image is exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.36,0:35:18.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是个令人费解之谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a puzzling mystery to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.40,0:35:19.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它让许多人感到困惑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It makes many wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.82,0:35:24.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们为什么永远看不到月球的另外一面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}why we never see another side of the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.41,0:35:32.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,经过了45亿年的演变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After 4.5 billion years of evolving,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.75,0:35:35.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地月系统已经到达了这一点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth-Moon system has arrived at a point
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.38,0:35:40.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球始终将同一个面露给我们看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the Moon shows us the same face all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.97,0:35:44.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,几十亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Billions of years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.39,0:35:46.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,火山潮汐所引起的摩擦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the friction created by volcanic tides
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.89,0:35:49.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,造成了月球减缓了自己的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}caused the Moon to slow its rotation
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.89,0:35:53.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,成为了对地球潮汐锁定了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and become tidally locked to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.65,0:35:55.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这并不意味我们的月球不在旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This doesn't mean our Moon isn't spinning,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.94,0:35:57.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是在几十亿年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it has slowed down
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.90,0:36:01.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,转的缓慢了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}considerably over billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.61,0:36:05.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球的秘密要隐藏在另外一面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the secret of the Moon's hidden far side
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.37,0:36:09.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就必须保持同步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has to do with synchronicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.04,0:36:11.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果这是地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If this is the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.62,0:36:14.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是我们所看到的月球的那一面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and if this is the side of the Moon that we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.92,0:36:17.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果月球不在旋转的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if the Moon were not rotating,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.80,0:36:24.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么 最终我们会看到月球的另外一面的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then, eventually, we would see the other side of the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.05,0:36:25.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为月球旋转的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because the Moon is rotating
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.22,0:36:28.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,与它围绕地球旋转的速度相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the same rate that it orbits the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.10,0:36:34.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同步旋转 所以我们就始终看到同一个面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}synchronous rotation, we always see the same side.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.44,0:36:38.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球的另外一面不总是黑暗的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The far side of the Moon is not always dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.03,0:36:41.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果到太空中你就能看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you were out in space, you'd be able to see that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.03,0:36:44.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳照射到月球的所有的面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun hits all sides of the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.78,0:36:49.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,伴随着月球围绕地球一个月长的轨道运行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the Moon makes its month-long orbit around the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.04,0:36:53.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而在我们所处的地方 我们就只能看到一个面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But from where we sit, we can only see one side.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.21,0:37:01.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力牢牢控制着地月关系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity is in firm control of the Earth-Moon relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.59,0:37:03.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.39,0:37:13.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把月球掌控在我们轨道上的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gravity that has held the Moon in our orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.89,0:37:16.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力正慢慢地失去控制…\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is slowly losing its grip...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.52,0:37:17.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其后果是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the consequences of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.02,0:37:20.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,足以让人看到月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are enough to make one look at the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.15,0:37:23.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发出全新的月光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a whole new light.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.86,0:37:30.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力是地球抓住月球的力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity is the force that holds the Moon to the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.83,0:37:34.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,正像运动员拉住… 链球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as this athlete is bound to the...hammer
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.79,0:37:36.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,围绕着自己的身体旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is orbiting about his body,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.62,0:37:39.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此引力将月球与地球栓在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so gravity binds the Moon and the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.67,0:37:41.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果引力突然消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if gravity all of a sudden went away,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.63,0:37:43.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么月球就将飞到太空中去了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Moon would fly off into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.84,0:37:48.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就象这个链球飞出场地一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just as this hammer flies off over the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.52,0:37:55.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当然 引力的作用永远不会终止的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of course, gravity never stops working.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.06,0:37:59.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而月球会以某种方式悄悄挣脱对其的控制吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but could the Moon somehow slip loose of its grip?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.86,0:38:07.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实是月球一直在慢慢地游离我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The truth is the Moon has always been slowly slipping away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.28,0:38:11.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球一直在不停地远离 而且它还在远离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon has been moving away, and it's still moving away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.87,0:38:13.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上月球远离我们的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, the Moon moves away from us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.20,0:38:15.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是每年两英寸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a couple of inches every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.37,0:38:18.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最后 月球将远离到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And eventually, the Moon is gonna be so far away
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.17,0:38:21.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不像我们现在所见到的月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it won't even seem like our Moon anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.38,0:38:25.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,打月球与地球相互交织在一起以来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ever since the Moon and Earth became intertwined,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.21,0:38:27.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球引力拽拉的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the energy from the Earth's gravitational tug
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.80,0:38:32.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一直在引起月球螺旋着逐渐远离我们的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been causing the Moon to spiral away from our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.89,0:38:34.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它目前正远离我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's currently moving away from us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.22,0:38:38.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以每年一到两英寸的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at a rate of one to two inches each year.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.44,0:38:40.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个意想不到的影响的关键\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The key to this unexpected effect
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.40,0:38:44.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在于由月球造成地球的潮汐隆起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the tidal bulges created on the Earth by the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.32,0:38:45.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球上的潮汐实际上是在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The tides on Earth actually act to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.44,0:38:51.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把月球推出去 每次绕地球运行都在旋转着 一步步远离地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to propel the Moon outward, spiraling out further from the Earth every orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.03,0:38:54.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,原因是地球的自转要比月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The reason is because the Earth spins faster
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.54,0:38:56.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,围绕我们旋转来得快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the Moon orbits us. So...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.41,0:38:59.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以在月球拉起一个潮汐隆起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}after the Moon has pulled up a tidal bulge,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.12,0:39:00.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,造成高潮位后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}raised the high tide,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.25,0:39:03.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球的旋转和拉动稍微比它有点提前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth turns and pulls slightly ahead of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.13,0:39:06.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 就有那么一点点向前的力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, there's just a little bit of a forward
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.09,0:39:08.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们称之为扭矩 有那么一点点额外的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}force, we call it a torque, a little bit of an extra kick
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.59,0:39:10.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,非常细微的加速的反冲力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that speeds it up ever so slightly,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.59,0:39:12.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而随着时间的推移 不停的加速使得它跑得越来越快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but over time, that speeding up makes it go faster and faster, which,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.18,0:39:18.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在轨道上 就意味着它不停地旋转着 走得越来越远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in orbit, means it's going, spiraling further and further away.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.93,0:39:21.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着时间的推移 月球将扩大自己的轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over time the Moon will expand its orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.73,0:39:27.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,直到有那么一天 最终超出我们地球的引力范围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until someday it will finally be beyond our Earth's gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.49,0:39:30.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是科学家称没有理由为此恐慌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But scientists say there is no cause for panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.61,0:39:31.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还要经过相当长的时间后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Quite a bit of time will pass before
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.99,0:39:34.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球会走出我们的视野 脱离轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Moon is out of sight and out of orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.03,0:39:37.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,估计最终的离开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Estimated time of total departure,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.16,0:39:39.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将要500亿年的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 50 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.79,0:39:43.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而我们的太阳继续燃烧将不足100亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And our Sun will flame out in less than 10 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.51,0:39:49.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,纵贯历史月球给我们带来了欣喜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Throughout history, the Moon has delighted,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.51,0:39:52.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,惊奇 有时还有恐慌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}surprised, and sometimes terrified us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.01,0:39:54.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们地球的运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the movement of our Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.47,0:39:56.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能是月球之谜的起因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be the cause of this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.77,0:40:02.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球的另外一个秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another secret of the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.23,0:40:05.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,已经被记载到了古代的文献中了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been documented in ancient texts
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.31,0:40:07.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并一直为之震惊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and continues to amaze.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.48,0:40:11.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它通常每隔几年就会出现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it usually appears every few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.45,0:40:17.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在月全食期间 整个月球会戏剧性地改变颜色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During a total lunar eclipse, the full Moon dramatically changes colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.83,0:40:20.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,究竟是什么原因呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What causes this?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.37,0:40:22.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月食的道理很简单\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A lunar eclipse is very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.42,0:40:24.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它只是当地球走到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It just occurs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.50,0:40:26.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳与月球中间时才发生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the Earth gets between the Sun and the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.54,0:40:28.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以当地球遮挡时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So when Earth gets in the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.67,0:40:30.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球投下一个巨大的阴影\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth casts a giant shadow...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.51,0:40:33.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,阻挡了阳光照射到月球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that blocks the sunlight from reaching the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.72,0:40:35.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在月食的食甚时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the peak of this eclipse,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.68,0:40:39.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球完全进入到了地球的阴影即本影时颜色转变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Moon passes completely into Earth's shadow or umbra,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.70,0:40:42.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并不是人们所预料的全黑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and transforms, not to black,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.08,0:40:46.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是变成了血红色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as one might expect, but to a blood red.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.44,0:40:51.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,结果是一些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What happens is some of the sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.28,0:40:52.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被地球阻挡的阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's being blocked by the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.86,0:40:55.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,实际上是经过了大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually slips through the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.41,0:40:58.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,红光通过得最好\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the red light gets through the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.41,0:41:00.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,阳光经过地球的大气层时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the Sun's rays pass through the Earth's atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.70,0:41:02.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会稍微有点弯曲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they are bent a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.58,0:41:06.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,红光经过这样的弯曲 使得它越过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the red rays are bent in such a way that they make it over the...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.08,0:41:10.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,越过地球的表面照亮月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over the surface of the Earth and illuminate the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.30,0:41:11.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只有红色或橙色的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when only red or orange light
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.01,0:41:13.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,到达月球的表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reaches the lunar surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.01,0:41:18.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球就呈现出红色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Moon appears red,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.14,0:41:22.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,另外一种光学现象平添了月球的神秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another optical phenomenon that adds to the Moon's mystique.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.23,0:41:24.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那个神秘感部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And part of that mystique
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.60,0:41:30.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可以归因于月球戏剧性地出现在我们的上方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can be attributed to the dramatic presence of the Moon above us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.57,0:41:35.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它在夜空中让其它的天体相形见绌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It outshines every other celestial body in the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.24,0:41:39.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球有着特别的魔法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a special magic to the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.24,0:41:41.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它那变化着的月相\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its changing phases,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.41,0:41:47.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在夜空中高挂闪亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its brightness in a otherwise dark sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.88,0:41:52.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 我们也能在白天看到月亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we also see the Moon during the daytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.34,0:41:54.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是什么原因？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.59,0:41:56.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其实很容易理解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's actually very easy to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.38,0:41:58.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为什么能在白天看到月亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}why we can see the Moon during the daylight.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.97,0:42:00.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以在家里来示范一下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can do this demonstration at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.76,0:42:03.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你所需要的就是将明亮的光源作为太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All you need is a bright light to act as the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.27,0:42:05.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一只水果作为月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a piece of fruit to act as the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.48,0:42:07.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我的脸就作为地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My face is acting as the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.19,0:42:10.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被照亮的部分是白天的部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The lit-up side is the daylight side,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.56,0:42:12.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,阴影部分是夜晚的部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the part in shadow is the nighttime side.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.98,0:42:15.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在月球当然围绕着地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the Moon, of course, orbits the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.11,0:42:18.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在其运行的一个月里的某些时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and at some of the times during the month in its orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.45,0:42:20.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,月球处在白昼的那一边\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's on the daylight side of the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.87,0:42:23.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我就能够在白天看到它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So I'm able to see it in full daylight.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.92,0:42:36.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上有许多行星和恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Actually, many planets and stars
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.09,0:42:38.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是在白天在我们的上空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are just above us during the daytime
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.76,0:42:41.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是太阳光确实是那么的明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the light from the Sun is just so bright
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.30,0:42:44.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,让它们几乎看不出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it obscures nearly all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.31,0:42:47.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只有月亮 它比最近的恒星亮10万倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only the Moon, which is 100,000 times brighter than the nearest star,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.81,0:42:51.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能透出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shines through.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.15,0:42:53.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在白天我们不总是能看到月亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't always see the Moon during the day
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.40,0:42:56.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为它不停地围绕着地球运转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it's constantly moving around our Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.24,0:43:00.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它不可能在每天的同一时间呆在同一个位置上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's not in the same position at the same time everyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.32,0:43:05.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过在地球的某个地方 它始终能够被看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, somewhere on the planet, it's always visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.20,0:43:08.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 尽管已经有所认识 但并非月球的所有的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But as we learned, not everything about the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.83,0:43:11.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都能够很容易得到解释或理解了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is easy to explain, or understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.00,0:43:16.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还有大量的问题尚未解决\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are still plenty of questions left unanswered.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.17,0:43:17.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,自有记载的历史开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's been part of the Moon's mystique,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.80,0:43:21.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就一直存在着月球之谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}since history was first recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.09,0:43:23.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们永远紧贴着我们的邻居\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are forever tight to our neighbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.35,0:43:26.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 我们对关联却知之甚少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we know so little about that dependence.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.64,0:43:28.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能还有其它正在发生的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There could be other things that are happening
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.27,0:43:31.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可是我们至今尚不知晓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we just don't know about yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.19,0:43:35.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大约会在下个世纪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over the next century or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.82,0:43:43.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为科学将带领我们进一步地弄明白它的奥秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think that science is going to...take us further into understanding its mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.87,0:43:53.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们是否会完全认识它呢？ 我对此表示怀疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whether we will fully understand it? I doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.13,0:43:54.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当然我不认为认识了所有的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Certainly I don't think we know everything
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.38,0:43:55.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是认识了月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is to know about the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.63,0:43:57.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有大量的东西需要去认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is a tremendous amount to learn,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.30,0:44:05.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是幸亏它在附近 我们在未来可进一步探索和了解它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but...fortunately it's within reach it and we will go exploring it at further and learn a lot more about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.93,0:44:12.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,更彻底地探索月球世界之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until we will our efforts to explore the lunar world more thoroughly...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.02,0:44:17.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们可能永远都不会知道所有秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we may never know all the secrets,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.11,0:44:20.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或希望解决隐藏的月球之谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or hope to solve the hidden mysteries of the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.00,0:44:27.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢观赏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks For Viewing
